        "action": "Remove time limit on appeals when new mental health information is available",
        "additional_details": "The Government should remove the time limits to start an appeal for cases where new information relating to the mental health of a defendant is available and may impact the case.",
        "background": "It can take years for some people to get their mental health diagnosed properly and it could be too late to appeal by then.",
